responses.gpt4: Creatinine is a waste product that your body produces when it breaks down protein, especially muscle tissue. Your kidneys are responsible for filtering creatinine and other waste products out of your blood. A creatinine test measures how well your kidneys are working by assessing how efficiently creatinine is being filtered out. This helps your doctor monitor your kidney health.
